1. e4 c6 { The Caro-Kann. Black prepares d5 with a solid pawn structure and
keeps the light squared bishop free. } 2. d4 (2. Nc3 d5 3. Nf3 Bg4 4. h3
Bxf3 5. Qxf3 e6 6. d4 dxe4 7. Nxe4 Nd7 8. Bd3 Ngf6 9. Nxf6+ Nxf6) 2... d5
3. e5 (3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 { The classical move. Black develops the
bishop outside the pawn chain before playing e6. } 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. h4 h6
7. Nf3 Nd7 8. h5 Bh7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 e6) (3. exd5 cxd5 4. Bd3 Nc6
5. c3 Nf6 6. Bf4 Bg4 7. Qb3 Na5 8. Qa4+ Bd7 9. Qc2 e6) 3... Bf5 { Against
the Advance, the bishop must leave the pawn chain before e6 locks it in. }
4. Nf3 (4. Bd3 Bxd3 5. Qxd3 e6 6. Nf3 Nd7 7. O-O Ne7) 4... e6 5. Be2 Nd7
6. O-O Ne7 { The knight heads for f5 where it hits the d4 pawn. } 7. Nbd2
